description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant Orthopaedic Surgeon: Foot and Ankle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;10 PAs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent Post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;AAC Date: Friday 27th November PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited for a Consultant Orthopaedic Surgeon specialising in Foot and Ankle. This is a full-time (10 PAs) post in the Trauma &amp; Orthopaedic Department on a permanent basis. The successful candidate will work with 15 other orthopaedic surgeons to provide a service to a catchment area of approx. 450,000. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The appointee will have a proven subspeciality interest in foot and ankle surgery; a second subspecialty interest would be welcomed to compliment the department. The department operates activity cross-site therefore clinical/outpatient work are required on both hospital sites. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust has a strong commitment to undergraduate and postgraduate education and the candidate should also be able to demonstrate previous commitment in this area. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust is a large acute trust providing a full range of secondary care services to people living in parts of south west London and Surrey. In addition, we provide more specialist services, in particular renal and neonatal intensive care, to a wider area, extending to parts of Sussex and Hampshire. We see approximately 700,000 patients annually. We serve a population of 450,000 people. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be on the GMC Specialist Register or be within 6 months of their expected CCT date at the time of the interview. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Christopher Hulme - Clinical Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;christopher.hulme@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
